15 WHEREAS, the longstanding bonds of friendship and economic ties
16 between the U.S. and the Republic of China (Taiwan), embodied in the
17 Taiwan Relations Act of 1979, continue to yield important economic,
18 social, strategic, and cultural benefits; and
19 WHEREAS, in 2024 Taiwan ranked 4th on the Heritage Foundation’s
20 Index of Economic Freedom, holds an important position in the global
21 economy as a top player in the world’s information and
22 communications technology industry, and is a trusted partner for
23 economic cooperation and exchanges in industries like smart
