10 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE 1ST SESSION
11 OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
12 CONCURRING THEREIN:
13 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature expresses support for
14 strengthening our partnership with Taiwan, for the expansion of
15 Taiwan’s role on the global stage, and for its efforts to preserve
16 peace and stability in the Taiwan Strait through meaningful
17 dialogue.
18 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature supports a tax agreement
19 between the United States and Taiwan.
20 THAT the Oklahoma State Legislature celebrates the 46th
21 anniversary of the Taiwan Relations Act of 1979 and the 45th
22 anniversary of the sister-state relationship between the State of
23 Oklahoma and Taiwan, and supports the establishment of an Oklahoma
24 Trade and Investment Office in Taiwan.
